//www.raqib50.com/parliaments/3/members/96/attendance_and_committees|title=\u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0645 \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0646\u062f\u0631\u064a  - \u0645\u0633\u062a\u0642\u064a\u0644|access-date=2017-08-21|language=ar}}</ref>\n* National Human Resources' Development Committee\n* Woman and Family Committee\n* Human Rights Committee\n* Committee of the Draft Answer to the Emiri Speech\n* Legislative and Legal Affairs Committee\n* Education, Culture and Guidance Committee\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kanderi, Abdulkarim}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of Kuwait]]\n[[Category:Middle Eastern politician stubs]]\n[[Category:Kuwaiti people stubs]]\n[[Category:Kuwait University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Strasbourg alumni]]\n\n\n{{Kuwait-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Abdulkarim Al-Kanderi\n| image = \n| caption = \n| native_name = \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0646\u062f\u0631\u064a\n| native_name_lang = ar\n| birth_date = 1981\n| residence = {{Flag|Kuwait}}\n| citizenship = {{Flag|Kuwait}}\n| education = Ph.D. in Commercial Law, Master of Commercial Law, Bachelor of Law.\n| alma_mater = [[Kuwait University]], [[University of Strasbourg]].\n| occupation = Politician, assistant professor.\n| known_for = Member of Parliament of the Kuwait Parliament.\n| organization = Kuwait Lawyers Association, University of Strasbourg Center of Commercial Law.\n| children = \n}}\n'''Abdulkarim Abdullah Al-Kanderi''' ([[Arabic]]: \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0646\u062f\u0631\u064a) (born 1981) is a politician, who is an elected [[Member of parliament|Member of Parliament]] of the [[Kuwait National Assembly Building|Kuwait Parliament]]. Al-Kanderi was first elected in the [[2013 Kuwaiti general election|Kuwaiti General Election 2013]], he won the tenth chair in the third constituency by 1,424 votes. However, he resigned when he found the government is not cooperative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aljarida.com/articles/1462328508807276300/|title=\u0627\u0644\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633 \u064a\u0642\u0628\u0644 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0627\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u062f\u0633\u0627\u0646\u064a \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u064a\u0639\u0627\u0646 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0643\u0646\u062f\u0631\u064a \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0631\u0627\u0634\u062f \u0648\u0635\u0641\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u0627\u0634\u0645... \u0648\u064a\u0639\u0644\u0646 \u062e\u0644\u0648 \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0639\u062f\u0647\u0645|website=www.aljarida.com|language=ar|access-date=2017-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.alaan.cc/pagedetails.asp?nid=185736&cid=30#.WZsOYpMjH_Q|title=\u0627\u062d\u062a\u062c\u0627\u062c\u0627\u064b \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0634\u0637\u0628 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u062c\u0648\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0648\u0645\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0633\u0627\u062a \u062f\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u062e\u0627\u0637\u0626\u0629|website=Alaan Online Newspaper|access-date=2017-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821212707/http://www.alaan.cc/pagedetails.asp?nid=185736&cid=30#.WZsOYpMjH_Q|archive-date=2017-08-21|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kuwaitnews.com/kuwait/parliament/64139-2014-04-30-12-50-13|title=\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0627\u0644\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u062f\u0633\u0627\u0646\u064a \u0648\u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0646\u062f\u0631\u064a \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u064a\u0639\u0627\u0646 \u0645\u0646 \u0639\u0636\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0629|last=\u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646\u064a|first=\u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0631\u0631|date=2014-04-30|work=\