lease: June 19, 2017\n*Format: Digital download, streaming\n*Label: N/A\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Xanarchy''\n|\n*Release: August 1, 2017\n*Format: Digital download, streaming\n*Label: N/A\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Xanarchy Militia''\n|\n*Release: November 14, 2018\n*Format: Digital download, streaming\n*Label: [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Fireworks''\n|\n*Release: February 19, 2019\n*Format: Streaming\n*Label: [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certification\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br><ref name=\"Hot 1002\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br />R&B/<br />HH]]<br><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/r-b-hip-hop-songs/2017-12-16 |title=Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs |work=Billboard |date=December 16, 2017 |accessdate=October 21, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-hot-100/2017-12-16|title=Canadian Hot 100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/netdata/ghl002.mbr/lista?liid=215&dfom=20180209|title=Veckolista Heatseeker \u2013 Vecka 7, 16 februari 2018|trans-title=Weekly chart Heatseeker \u2013 Week 7, 16 februari 2018|language=Swedish|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=October 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Montana Doe\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2016\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\" {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Who Are You?\"<br />{{small|(with Oohdem Beatz)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| ''CITGO''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Center Fold\"<br />{{small|(with Julian Dova and Oohdem Beatz)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"4\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Sorry\"<br />{{small|(with Oohdem Beatz)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Vicodin\"<br />{{small|(with Julian Dova and Oohdem Beatz)}}\n| rowspan=\"10\"| 2017\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Been Bout It\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Xanarchy\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"2\"|''Xanarchy''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"No Love\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Crash the Whip\"<br />{{small|(with $teven Cannon)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\" {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Slingshot\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"3\"|''[[Total Xanarchy]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Betrayed (Lil Xan song)|Betrayed]]\"\n| 64 || 28 || 49 || 11\n| \n*RIAA: Platinum<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=Lil+Xan&ti=Betrayed#search_section |title=American single certification \u2013 Lil Xan \u2013 Betrayed |publisher=Recording Industry Association of America |date=May 3, 2018 |accessdate=October 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Far\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Water (Models)\"<br />{{small|(with Spell Jordan featuring Smokeasac)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\" {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Wake Up\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\"|''[[Total Xanarchy]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Color Blind\"<br />{{small|(with [[Diplo]])}}\n| rowspan=\"7\"| 2018\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\"|''[[California (Diplo EP)|California]]'' and ''[[Total Xanarchy]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Man\"<br />{{small|(featuring $teven Cannon)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Total Xanarchy]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Moonlight\"<br />{{small|(with [[Charli XCX]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Lies\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[Lil Skies]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\"|''Heartbreak Soldiers''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Live or Die\"<br />{{small|(with [[Noah Cyrus]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\" {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Slope\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\"|''Xanarchy Militia''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"On Sight\"<br />{{small|(with Lucifena)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"3\" {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Watch Me Fall\"\n| rowspan=\"11\"| 2019\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Tree Sap\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Shake It\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"1\"|''Pornhub Valentine's Day Album''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Jewelry\"<br />{{small|(with DJ Stadium and PH4DE)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"8\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Summer Days\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"I Might\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[YBN Nahmir]], Steven Cannon and [[YBN Almighty Jay]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Bloody Nose\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Midnight In Prague\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"West Side\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Like Me\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Wrong Way\"<br />{{small|(with Kidd Keo)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n====As featured artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Lifeless\"<br />{{small|(Chem X featuring Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"5\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"For the Better\"<br />{{small|(Kid Kaze featuring Lil Xan)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Lost\"<br />{{small|(Joei Razook featuring Lil Xan)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Broke the Outline\"<br />{{small|(Kid Kaze featuring Lil Xan)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Whoa\"<br />{{small|(HenneyPapi featuring Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"9\"| 2018\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Racksonracksonracks\"<br />{{small|(HenneyPapi featuring Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"1\"|''Litlyfe II''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Wait\"<br />{{small|(Kid Kaze featuring Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Brainfreeze\"<br />{{small|(Prime Society featuring Lil Xan and $teven Cannon)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Crazy Shit\"<br />{{small|(Skooly featuring Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"1\"|''Don't You Ever Forget Me 3''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Percy\"<br />{{small|(Lil Icepack featuring Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Cookin'\"<br />{{small|(Blatz featuring $teven Cannon and Lil Xan)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"I Might\"<br />{{small|($teven Cannon featuring Lil Xan)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Swimming\"<br />{{small|(Baby Goth featuring [[Trippie Redd]] and Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"1\"|''Baby Goth''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"XOXO\"<br />{{small|([[Jumex (musician)|JUMEX]] featuring Lil Xan)}}\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2020\n| rowspan=\"1\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Nominated work !! Result !! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2018 || [[2018 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]] || Push Artist of the Year || rowspan=2|Lil Xan || {{nominated}} ||<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8478247/2018-mtv-ema-camila-cabello-ariana-grande-post-malone-nominees|title=Camila Cabello, Ariana Grande, Post Malone Lead 2018 MTV EMA Nominees|date=October 4, 2018|website=Billboard}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2018 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards]] || Best Push || {{nominated}} ||<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lil Xan}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n[[Category:American rappers of Mexican descent]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records artists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mumble rappers]]\n[[Category:People from Redlands, California]]\n[[Category:Rappers from California]]\n[[Category:West Coast hip hop musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American rapper from California}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Lil Xan\n| background       = solo_singer<!--includes rappers-->\n| image            = File:Lil Xan.png\n| caption          = Lil Xan performing in Berkeley in 2018\n| birth_name       = Nicholas Diego Leanos\n| alias            = {{hlist|Lil Xan|Diego}}\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1996|9|6}}\n| birth_place      = [[Redlands, California]], U.S.\n| origin           = \n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]]|[[cloud rap]]|[[emo rap]]|[[SoundCloud rap]]<ref>[https://www.thestranger.com/music/2018/01/24/25745423/lil-xan-is-the-new-face-of-sad-rap Lil Xan Is the New Face of Sad! Rap - Music - The Stranger<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref name=kulturehub>{{cite web|url=https://kulturehub.com/lil-xan-anti-xanax/|title=Who is Lil Xan? The Cali rapper is the new leader of the anti-Xanax movement|author=Kasra Ahmadi|date=2017-12-20|access-date=2018-06-16|language=en-US|quote=Diego hasn\u2019t turned back since, and is now becoming one of the quickest viral SoundCloud rappers in the game.}}</ref>|[[pop music|pop]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Rapper|singer|songwriter}}\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rockstardreams.com/2017/11/15/lil-xan-signs-with-colombia-records/|title=Lil Xan Signs with Columbia Records|website=Rockstar Dreams|author=D.L.|date=November 15, 2017|accessdate=November 29, 2017}}</ref>\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|$teven Cannon|[[Charli XCX]]|[[Diplo]]|[[Noah Cyrus]]|[[Lil Skies]]}}\n| website          = [https://xanarchygang.com/ xanarchygang.com]\n}}\n\n'''Nicholas Diego Leanos'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bsc1QXnnR8e/|author=xanxiety|title=fuck it i\u2019ll do a Q n A on live rn|date=January 10, 2019|website=[[Instagram]]|access-date=January 13, 2019}}</ref> (born September 6, 1996), better known as '''Lil Xan''' ({{IPAc-en|z|\u00e6|n}} {{Respell|ZANN}}) or simply '''Diego''', is an American [[Rapping|rapper]], [[Singing|singer]] and [[songwriter]] of Mexican descent from [[Redlands, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8061630/hottest-latino-mcs-hip-hop-today|title=10 Hottest MCs of Latin Descent in Hip-Hop Today|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Elibert|first=Mark|date=December 5, 2017|accessdate=December 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/18/arts/music/eminem-g-eazy-lil-xan-nf.html|title=3 Rappers Peeking at Eminem's Playbook|work=[[The New York Times]]|last=Caramanica|first=Jon|date=December 18, 2017|accessdate=December 20, 2017}}</ref> He is best known for his song \"[[Betrayed (Lil Xan song)|Betrayed]]\", which was certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/lil-xans-betrayed-has-gone-platinum-news.49606.html|title=Lil Xan's \"Betrayed\" Has Gone Platinum|work=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2018-05-10}}</ref> and peaked at number 64 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. On April 6, 2018, Leanos released his debut studio album, ''[[Total Xanarchy]]''. His sophomore album, ''Sorry I Didn't Quit'', is due for release in 2020.\n\nHis stage name is derived from Xanax, the trade name of the prescription drug [[alprazolam]].\n\n==Early life==\nLeanos was born on September 6, 1996, in [[Redlands, California]], to Mexican parents.<ref name=\"Vibe\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vibe.com/2018/03/who-is-lil-xan/|title=10 Things You Should Know About Lil Xan|last=Brown|first=Preezy|date=March 24, 2018|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|accessdate=April 5, 2018}}</ref> Growing up, Leanos was poor and lived in motels most of his childhood.<ref name=\":0\"/> He attended [[Redlands East Valley High School]], but dropped out of high school in his freshman year, and spent several years at home unemployed.<ref>{{cite interview|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s0zJub4oD-g|title=The LIL XAN Interview|author=Back2Back Hip Hop|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=August 11, 2017|accessdate=November 29, 2017}}</ref><ref name=nojumper>{{cite interview|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XzXBq8KCw8I|title=The Lil Xan Interview|publisher=YouTube|author=No Jumper|date=January 27, 2018|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref> Leanos took a job as a street cleaner and sold drugs<ref>{{Citation|title=Lil Xan Would Like to Make You Sober: Noisey Raps|date=December 15, 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LGLpAdzqGtk|author=Noisey|publisher=YouTube|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref> before he began rapping.<ref name=\"Billboard2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8094303/lil-xan-betrayed-you-should-know-video-interview|title=Get to Know 'Betrayed' Rapper Lil Xan|last=Schiller|first=Rebecca|date=January 16, 2018|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=January 19, 2018}}</ref> Leanos later pursued a photography career in support of several friends who were rappers. He eventually had his camera stolen, and chose to begin rapping in lieu of investing in a new camera.<ref name=\"XXL2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/11/the-break-presents-lil-xan/|title=The Break Presents: Lil Xan|last=C.M.|first=Emmanuel|date=November 10, 2017|website=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|accessdate=November 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nLeanos began to gain recognition through platforms such as [[SoundCloud]] and [[YouTube]]. His popularity grew after the release of the music video for his song \"Betrayed\" in August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8014759/pandora-predictions-lil-xan-lyrica-anderson-mahalia|title=Pandora Predictions to Know: Lil Xan, Lyrica Anderson & Mahalia|last=Blake|first=Emily|date=October 26, 2017|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 12, 2017}}</ref> The song peaked at {{Abbr|no.|Number}} 64 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref name=\"Hot 1002\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/2018-02-17|title=Billboard Hot 100: February 17, 2018|date=|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 13, 2018}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]'', Leanos announced his debut album ''[[Total Xanarchy]]''.<ref name=\"XXL2\" /> The album includes collaborations with artists such as [[Diplo]] and [[Swae Lee]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8094841/lil-xan-betrayed-interview-chartbreaker|title=Chartbreaker: Lil Xan on Face Tattoos and Overcoming Addiction|last=Haithcoat|first=Rebecca|date=January 22, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref> In December 2017, Leanos announced his ''Total Xanarchy'' tour,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/lil-xan-reveals-dates-for-total-xanarchy-tour-news.41208.html|title=Lil Xan Reveals Dates For \"Total Xanarchy\" Tour|last=F|first=Matt|date=December 21, 2017|work=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref> which sold out in five hours according to ''Billboard''.<ref name=\":0\" /> In 2018, Leanos considered changing his stage name to '''Diego''' in order to support his anti-drug message,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/01/lil-xan-plans-changing-name/|title=Lil Xan Plans on Changing His Name|last=Coleman II|first=C. Vernon|date=January 13, 2018|publisher=XXL|accessdate=January 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/lil-xan-officially-changes-name-to-diego-on-big-boys-neighborhood-news.42216.html|title=Lil Xan Officially Changes Name To Diego On Big Boy's Neighborhood|last=P.|first=Milca|date=January 14, 2018|publisher=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=January 15, 2018}}</ref> however he has since expressed uncertainty toward officially going through with the pseudonym change.<ref name=nojumper/>\n\nLeanos released his debut studio album, ''Total Xanarchy'' on April 6, 2018. Despite receiving generally negative reviews, it was a moderate commercial success, debuting at number ten on the ''Billboard'' 200.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2018/04/lil-xan-total-xanarchy-album/|title=Lil Xan Shares 'Total Xanarchy' Album - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2018-11-14}}</ref> The following month in May 2018, Leanos announced the mixtape ''Heartbreak Soldiers''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/lil-xan-shares-heartbreak-soldiers-tracklist-and-release-date-news.51389.html|title=Lil Xan Shares \"Heartbreak Soldiers\" Tracklist & Release Date|work=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2018-11-14}}</ref> which was released on July 8, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hypebeast.com/2018/7/lil-xan-heartbreak-soldiers-ep-stream|title=Lil Xan Surprises Fans With New 'Heartbreak Soldiers' Project|work=HYPEBEAST|access-date=2018-11-14}}</ref> In September 2018, Leanos announced he had been working on an album titled ''Be Safe'' as a tribute to [[Mac Miller]], as these were the last words he said to Leanos before his death.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/09/lil-xan-says-mac-miller-inspired-title-of-his-next-project|title=Lil Xan Says Mac Miller's Last Words to Him Inspired the Title of His Next Project|last=Jarreau|first=Khal|date=September 26, 2018|website=Complex|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927114429/https://www.complex.com/music/2018/09/lil-xan-says-mac-miller-inspired-title-of-his-next-project|archive-date=September 27, 2018|url-status=live|access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/lil-xan-is-making-a-mac-miller-tribute-album.html|title=Lil Xan Is Making a Mac Miller Tribute Album|last=Harris|first=Hunter|work=Vulture|access-date=2018-11-14|language=en}}</ref>\n\nLeanos initially planned on releasing his ''Be Safe'' project in 2019, but the album entered production limbo and was ultimately never released. In November 2019, he announced his next album would be titled ''When September Ends'' and released an accompanying album cover, but this also never came to fruition.<ref>https://people.com/music/lil-xan-quit-xanax-cold-turkey-had-seizures/</ref> In January 2020, Leanos announced his next album would be titled ''Sorry I Didn't Quit'', and is due for release sometime in 2020.<ref>https://genius.com/albums/Lil-xan/Sorry-i-didnt-quit</ref><ref>https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2019/12/lil-xa-not-quitting-rap/</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\nLeanos has listed [[Pharrell Williams]] and [[N.E.R.D]] as early influences in [[Hip hop music|hip hop]], with other influences including [[Arctic Monkeys]], [[Cage the Elephant]] and [[Queens of the Stone Age]].<ref name=\"Pigeons&Planes2\">{{Cite news|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/interviews/2017/12/lil-xan-interview-2017|title=People Can Change: An Interview With Lil Xan|last=Rindner|first=Grant|date=December 22, 2017|work=Pigeons & Planes|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref> Leanos has also described [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] and [[Mac Miller]] as musical inspirations.<ref name=\"Billboard2\" />\n\nAccording to ''Pigeons & Planes'', Leanos' music started off as \"typical trap\" and later shifted towards \"a murkier, dream-like sound\".<ref name=\"Pigeons&Planes2\" /> ''[[The New Yorker]]'' has described Leanos as part of a \"sad rap\" movement.<ref>\"{{cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/01/08/lil-xan-and-the-year-in-sad-rap|title=Lil Xan and the Year in Sad Rap|last=Battan|first=Carrie|date=January 8, 2018|work=[[The New Yorker]]|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLeanos started dating singer and actress [[Noah Cyrus]] on June 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/dont-accept-noah-cyrus-rapper-lil-xan-go-public-fans-arent-happy-220117784.html|title='I don't accept this': Noah Cyrus and rapper Lil Xan go public, and fans aren't happy about it|access-date=2018-07-31|language=en-US}}</ref> The couple released the collaboration \"Live or Die\" in August 2018. They broke up in September 2018, with both parties accusing the other of being unfaithful; Leanos also claimed that the relationship was forced by the couple's record label, Columbia.<ref>{{Citation|last=adam22|title=Lil Xan speaks on Noah Cyrus, Mac Miller and quitting music|date=2018-09-08|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i9H5-aXfyRQ|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> However, weeks later he appeared to walk back this claim in an interview on ''Open Late with Peter Rosenberg'', stating \"Honest to God, I would say like most of the reason the breakup happened was because of me. It was my fault. We could have still been together, but I just feel like I fucked everything up. It also put me in a darker place because I was getting slammed left and right.\" He went on to say that he had \"nothing but love for the Cyrus family.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/why-did-lil-xan-break-up-with-noah-cyrus-the-rapper-admitted-it-was-his-fault-12062673|title=Lil Xan Just Admitted His Breakup With Noah Cyrus Was His Fault For A Sad Reason|last=Boyle|first=Kelli|date=September 27, 2018|website=Elite Daily|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130161856/https://www.elitedaily.com/p/why-did-lil-xan-break-up-with-noah-cyrus-the-rapper-admitted-it-was-his-fault-12062673|archive-date=January 30, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nLeanos has been open about his former [[addiction]] to [[benzodiazepine]]s (particularly [[alprozolam|Xanax]]) as well as [[opiate]]s. He was able to overcome his Xanax problem after two years of suffering from addiction.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|url=https://djbooth.net/features/2017-10-19-lil-xan-xanax-addiction|title=A Rapper Named Lil Xan Talks About His Painful Xanax Addiction & Recovery|date=October 19, 2017|work=DJBooth|accessdate=November 29, 2017}}</ref> Leanos currently speaks out against Xanax abuse and urges people to stop using the drug altogether.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/lil-xan-interview/|title=Lil Xan Is the Unlikely Inspiration for Getting Kids off Xanax|last=Hodge|first=Kyle|date=January 18, 2018|publisher=[[Highsnobiety]]|accessdate=January 19, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=http://trl.mtv.com/news/3057388/lil-xan-on-substance-abuse-in-rap/|title=Lil Xan On Substance Abuse In The Hip-Hop Community: 'You'd Be Stupid To Keep Glorifying It'|last=Gore|first=Sydney|date=January 9, 2018|publisher=[[Total Request Live|TRL]]|accessdate=January 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2019, Leanos announced that he and his then-fianc\u00e9e Annie Smith were expecting a child.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/au/news/1015931/lil-xan-expecting-his-first-child-5-months-after-noah-cyrus-breakup|title=Lil Xan Expecting His First Child 5 Months After Noah Cyrus Breakup|last=Grossman|first=Lena|date=February 17, 2019|website=E! News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218090558/https://www.eonline.com/au/news/1015931/lil-xan-expecting-his-first-child-5-months-after-noah-cyrus-breakup|archive-date=February 18, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=February 18, 2019}}</ref> On April 6, Smith revealed that she had experienced a [[miscarriage]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/ca/news/1030377/lil-xan-s-fiancee-reveals-she-had-a-miscarriage|title=Lil Xan's Fianc\u00e9e Reveals She Had a Miscarriage|date=April 6, 2019|website=E! News|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-04-07}}</ref> sharing the information about the incident via a video and photographs on Instagram.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/ca/news/1030377/lil-xan-s-fiancee-reveals-she-had-a-miscarriage|title=Lil Xan's Fianc\u00e9e Reveals She Had a Miscarriage|date=April 6, 2019|website=E! News|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-04-07}}</ref>  However, in a ''[[Adam22|No Jumper]]'' interview weeks later, Leanos revealed he had suspicions that Smith had been faking her pregnancy; this came about after a number of the rapper's fans on social media pointed out that the couples' ultrasound photos looked identical to ones that could be found on Google.<ref>https://people.com/music/lil-xan-questions-annie-smith-faked-pregnancy-miscarriage/</ref> The pair eventually separated, with Leanos later claiming the relationship had been toxic and that he continued to doubt the authenticity of her pregnancy. He began dating [[YouTube]] vlogger Gabby Parsons in November 2019.<ref>https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/lil-xan-is-all-over-off-his-new-girlfriend-in-soft-ig-post-news.96965.html</ref> Leanos stated in a comment on Parsons\u2019 instagram, \u201cAfter I had the siezures and almost died I finally woke up and realized what was most important in life and that\u2019s god, family, and love! And I have never had a stronger connection with anyone but Gabby so yes we are talking and it\u2019s a very healthy relationship\u201d.<ref> https://www.instagram.com/p/B4_cEIPHWNO/?igshid=v0sjvikskxat</ref> Their relationship was confirmed in Parsons\u2019 vlog when the couple happily stated \u201cIt\u2019s public!\u201d regarding the status and confirmation of their relationship. Since the start of their relationship, Leanos publicly appeared to be taking his sobriety and happiness more seriously that he had previously.\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8337801/cardi-b-invasion-of-privacy-debuts-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-album-chart|title=Cardi B's 'Invasion of Privacy' Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=April 15, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 16, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Total Xanarchy]]''\n|\n*Release: April 6, 2018\n*Formats: CD, digital download\n*Label: [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| 10\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Sorry I Didn't Quit''\n|\n*Release: TBD\n*Formats: CD, digital download\n*Label: [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| \u2014\n|}\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Mixtape details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Heartbreak Soldiers''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/lilxanfuhyobih/status/981431173388828677|title=LIL XAN on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=2018-05-08}}</ref>\n|\n*Release: July 8, 2018\n*Format: Digital download, streaming\n*Label: [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Heartbreak Soldiers Pt. 2''\n|\n*Release: March 20, 20